.TH cando-dump-messages 1  "cando-dump-messages 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
cando\-dump\-messages \- Message Dump Utility \- Comprehensive view of CAN messages and signals
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcando\-dump\-messages\fR [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-csv\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-protocol\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-comments\fR] [\fB\-e\fR|\fB\-\-enums\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-full\fR] [\fB\-\-rust\-names\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Message Dump Utility \- Comprehensive view of CAN messages and signals
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: text]
Output format: text, csv, or json
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
Shortcut for CSV output
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Shortcut for JSON output
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-protocol\fR \fI<PROTOCOL>\fR [default: all]
Protocol to display: j1939 or all
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-comments\fR
Show DBC comments and signal descriptions
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-enums\fR
Show value descriptions (enumerations)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show verbose output with all metadata (implies \-\-comments and \-\-enums)
.TP
\fB\-\-full\fR
Show full output with all available metadata and formatting
.TP
\fB\-\-rust\-names\fR
Output Rust snake_case field names instead of DBC PascalCase names
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
